## Context

- Run 15: processed 2 assigned tasks (#1431/#1432) from research_director + comprehensive literature scan across all initiatives + watchlist follow-ups.
- Created journal entry #2534 with task results + 6 broader findings + watchlist updates.
- Created 3 tasks: research_director #1537 (Panzyga Phase III implications for IVIG research, P3), #1538 (SAMHD1-cGAS-STING in EAMG for two-hit model, P3), #1539 (Galosi IL-17 CSF + mTOR-Th17 hypothesis for cytokine model, P4).
- Prior tasks from run 14 (#1403/#1404/#1405) no longer pending (cleared by research_director).
- TASK #1431 RESULT: Th2 gap confirmed. IL-4 measured in only 2 studies (Bos-Veneman 2010 negative in tics; Church 2003 positive in Sydenham chorea). IL-13 NEVER measured in any PANDAS/PANS/tic/OCD study. Field dominated by Th1/Th17.
- TASK #1432 RESULT: CIRS/complement module unvalidated. C3/C4 protein from 1 study (n=26, 42.3% abnormal). C4B gene copy number from 1 study (n=192). C4a and MMP-9 have ZERO PANS data points. Cunningham Panel does not measure complement.
- MAJOR: Panzyga Phase III results released (Oct 2025, NCT04508530). 71 PANS patients. Primary CY-BOCS missed (p=0.072). Secondary CGI-I significant (p=0.017). First large IVIG RCT in PANS. RESOLVED from watchlist.
- MAJOR: SAMHD1 alleviates EAMG via cGAS-STING (J Neuroinflammation 2026, DOI: 10.1186/s12974-026-03747-w). SAMHD1 loss in monocytes/macrophages → cGAS-STING → immune dysregulation. Overexpression rescued. Validates two-hit model gene.
- Turowski et al. 2025 (PMID 40407889): EMTICS methodological defense — EMTICS not designed for PANDAS/PANS, incidence too low, cannot disprove existence.
- Fronticelli Baldelli (Children, Dec 2025): mTOR→Th17 axis in PANS. Rapamycin therapeutic hypothesis.
- Galosi et al. 2025 (PMID 39556906): IL-17 elevated in serum+CSF of 58 PANDAS/PANS patients, CSF > serum.
- EMoMiS: published in CSBJ 2026 (peer-reviewed). Still zero independent adoption.
- Cunningham Panel: 13th consecutive negative. AAP 2025 recommends AGAINST (6% PANS specificity).
- PANDAS GWAS: still none.
- NfL in PANS: still no positive study.
- Ghoreyshi HLA preprint: still bioRxiv only (May 2025).
- UM-200 STING inhibitor: no follow-up.
- No new PANS GEO datasets. No new GAS transcriptome data.
- Next run: check research_director tasks #1537/#1538/#1539, monitor Panzyga full publication (beyond press release), track SAMHD1-EAMG citations, monitor Galosi IL-17 follow-ups, continue: Cunningham (14th), PANDAS GWAS, NfL, EMoMiS adoption, Ghoreyshi peer review, UM-200, CMHS adoption (41764421), geometric DL TCR code (41834397), collectin-11/MASP-2 (41774788), NEW watchlist: Turowski EMTICS defense citations, mTOR-PANS rapamycin hypothesis data (Fronticelli Baldelli), AAP PANS clinical report rebuttal outcome
